some horse sashimi first!

569
00:21:58,647 --> 00:21:58,750
 

570
00:21:58,750 --> 00:22:00,581
Food again?

571
00:22:00,581 --> 00:22:00,919
 

572
00:22:00,919 --> 00:22:05,947
Next time on Descendants of Darkness:
The Devil's Trill, Part 1

573
00:22:05,947 --> 00:22:06,057
 

574
00:22:06,057 --> 00:22:09,891
Those who live in the darkness
wander aimlessly.

575
00:22:09,891 --> 00:22:18,837
 

576
00:22:18,837 --> 00:22:22,204
As I square the round edges
on the drink

577
00:22:22,204 --> 00:22:22,307
 

578
00:22:22,307 --> 00:22:25,242
I wait for you on the street corner

579
00:22:25,242 --> 00:22:25,343
 

580
00:22:25,343 --> 00:22:28,835
The liquid inside is warm
and I can't drink it anymore

581
00:22:28,835 --> 00:22:28,947
 

582
00:22:28,947 --> 00:22:31,541
But what can I do
but hold onto to it?

583
00:22:31,541 --> 00:22:31,649
 

584
00:22:31,649 --> 00:22:38,885
In the glass case reflecting me
in the darkness

585
00:22:38,885 --> 00:22:38,990
 

586
00:22:38,990 --> 00:22:45,623
There is a doll that has been
scowling at me

587
00:22:45,623 --> 00:22:59,077
 

588
00:22:59,077 --> 00:23:05,505
The tune I whistle is a
bright and cheerful one

589
00:23:05,505 --> 00:23:06,017
 

590
00:23:06,017 --> 00:23:11,956
A little noise dedicated
to the people of the world

591
00:23:11,956 --> 00:23:12,724
 

592
00:23:12,724 --> 00:23:19,061
No one could possibly
recognize the melody

593
00:23:19,061 --> 00:23:19,597
 

594
00:23:19,597 --> 00:23:25,001
But do you hear it?
Good-bye, LOVE ME
